								<div class="title" id="post-title-4111815">
																		Endings and beginnings have a lot in common, don&#039;t they?
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3440103&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252367" alt="Captain Kirby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3440103)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;" >Captain Kirby</a></span> <span class="odate time_1546885055 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Jan 2019 18:17</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4111815">
									

<p>And here it is. The end of the journey. I wanted to do it as a sort of tribute to the tale that started it all in doomcon, and I'm happy with how its turned out.</p>
<p>Thanks to DarkStuff, Uncle Nicolini, Othellothecat, mayoculpa and stormbreath for critique.</p>
<p>And thanks to you reader for sticking it out through this little series of mine.</p>
<p>If you want to read more of my works, you can find them <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/captain-kirby-s-personal-file">here!</a></p>

							</div>

								
